1. What is JavaScript?
?High-level, interpreted programming language.
?Runs in browsers (client-side) and Node.js (server-side / automation).
?Used for interactivity, automation scripts, APIs, and testing frameworks.
How to Run JS:
?Browser: Create index.html with <script src="app.js"></script>
?Node.js: node app.js
?Online: Use console in browser DevTools (F12)
